Subject: [PATCH 1/3] fix(desktop): add flatpak detection and resolution for Linux
 app lookup

`checkAppExists` always returned `true` on Linux without actually checking
if the app was installed. `resolveAppPath` returned the app name as-is,
but flatpak-installed apps need `flatpak run <app-id>` instead of a bare
binary name, since flatpak export directories often aren't on Electron's
PATH.

Changes:
- `checkAppExists` now checks PATH via `which` and falls back to `flatpak
  info` for known flatpak app IDs
- `resolveAppPath` returns the resolved binary path or a `flatpak run`
  command string
- Added `FLATPAK_APP_MAP` mapping common binary names to their flatpak
  application IDs

Fixes flatpak file associations in the "Open with" menu.

diff --git a/packages/desktop/src/main/apps.ts b/packages/desktop/src/main/apps.ts
index a93c14b..d95e84d 100644
--- a/packages/desktop/src/main/apps.ts
+++ b/packages/desktop/src/main/apps.ts
@@ -4,21 +4,46 @@ import util from "node:util"

 const execFilePromise = util.promisify(execFile)

+// Maps openWith binary names to their flatpak application IDs
+const FLATPAK_APP_MAP: Record<string, string> = {
+  code: "com.visualstudio.code",
+  cursor: "com.todesktop.230113mipedgjete8k7x",
+  zed: "dev.zed.Zed",
+  subl: "com.sublimetext.three",
+}
+
 const exists = (path: string) =>
   access(path)
     .then(() => true)
